    <problem>
        <title>P3</title>
            <p>
            Consider the equation 
            <me>1+3+5+\cdots+(2n-1)=n^2\, .
            </me>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Draw a picture that demonstrates why this is true for all positive integers <m>n</m>.
                        Explain how your picture is related to the equation.
                        (This is an "embodied" proof.)
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Give a "symbolic" proof of this equation by rewriting the numbers in the sum and using properties of sums that we have discussed in class.
                        Hint: write each odd number as <m>2k-1=k+(k-1)</m>.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
            <p>
                Hint: Begin both of these with small examples. 
                What happens when <m>n=1,2,3,4</m>?
                How can you use these examples to guide your thinking about the general case?
            </p>
        </p>
    </problem>

